        "### Practice 2\n",
        "\n",
        "Repeat the compression with thresholds $0.1$, $0.5$, and $1.0$. What happens to the number of nonzero coefficients and the reconstruction error?\n",
        "\n",
        "<details>\n",
        "<summary><strong>Show solution</strong></summary>"
      ],
      "id": "c64ed451"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "for threshold in [0.1, 0.5, 1.0]:\n",
        "    chat = c.copy()\n",
        "    chat[np.abs(chat) <= threshold] = 0\n",
        "    uhat = inverse_haar_transform(chat)\n",
        "    print(\"threshold =\", threshold)\n",
        "    print(\"nonzero coefficients =\", np.count_nonzero(chat))\n",
        "    print(\"error norm =\", np.linalg.norm(u-uhat))\n",
        "    print(np.round(uhat, 3))"
      ],
      "id": "7ed7b440",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "As the threshold increases, more coefficients are set to zero. The representation becomes more compressed, but the reconstruction error usually increases.\n",
        "\n",
        "</details>\n",
        "\n",
        "## Part 3: Two-dimensional Haar transform"
      ],
      "id": "7bed1513"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "def haar2(A):\n",
        "    A = np.asarray(A, dtype=float)\n",
        "    C = np.apply_along_axis(haar_transform, 1, A)\n",
        "    C = np.apply_along_axis(haar_transform, 0, C)\n",
        "    return C\n",
        "\n",
        "def inverse_haar2(C):\n",
        "    A = np.apply_along_axis(inverse_haar_transform, 0, C)\n",
        "    A = np.apply_along_axis(inverse_haar_transform, 1, A)\n",
        "    return A\n",
        "\n",
        "A = np.array([[70,56,61,49],\n",
        "              [52,46,39,43],\n",
        "              [63,45,46,54],\n",
        "              [53,39,40,44]], dtype=float)\n",
        "C = haar2(A)\n",
        "print(np.round(C, 2))\n",
        "print(np.round(inverse_haar2(C), 2))"
      ],
      "id": "b1a0c3bd",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
